data.name: labelFileManagement.Text
data.value: You can use these settings to manage your log and trace files, preventing them from accumulating and taking up much needed disk space. Any changes made to these options will take effect when you next start the diagnostic application.

data.name: labelSummaryLogFileSize.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum file size allowed for the Summary Log Files. Large summary files can cause tool problems and should be limited to less than 4 MB.

data.name: checkBoxDebug.ToolTip
data.value: Included by default. These messages provide status information from underlying layers in the application and are often useful in the diagnosis of device connection and programming issues.

data.name: label1.ToolTip
data.value: Action to take when the Summary Log File exceeds the specified Maximum. By default, the file will be renamed as an archived file.

data.name: checkBoxByte.ToolTip
data.value: Excluded by default. These messages should only be included if you are experiencing device connection issues as they can create very large trace files.

data.name: labelPanels.Text
data.value: You can use these settings to control how the diagnostic application loads and populates instrument, service routine, and parameter panels, and action dialogs.

data.name: useNameValuePairsToParameterize.Text
data.value: Use name/value pair to configure parameters.

data.name: checkBoxAdrAdditionalSaveLocation.Text
data.value: Save additional copies of Troubleshooting Reports to:

data.name: labelFilterLists.Text
data.value: &Filter instruments and parameters on "All List" panels as:

data.name: $this.HeaderText
data.value: You can use these settings to manage how the application provides technical support such as trace files and incident reports. These settings should only be modified when trying to resolve an issue with the diagnostic tool. It is recommended that you restart the diagnostic application after making changes to these settings.

data.name: checkBoxException.ToolTip
data.value: Included by default. These messages are rare but provide extremely useful information regarding exceptions that the diagnosis tools have handled. Installation and data file corruption can easily be found if these messages are included.
